Yes. But this is a school board you see. The school - schoolteachers learn you - way to garden. See and then you go and take a piece - off somebody else's garden. Now like the - off the railways
 for - you take a piece off of there, well they turn - put that into houses now, you see. Well we had that - over there we'd have it for sixpence a yard. See? Then there'd be two men come over - from the mill, and show you way to prune - prune trees. And 
- prune - gooseberry trees. See.
