Oh bugger yes. Yes I - if I seen a big boy knocking a small one I'd - I'd go over. Interfere. But I was the same when I was in the Army. When I joined the bloody Army. And - Canadians - was fighting. And - course this little ch
ap got one of 'em down on the ground, he was punc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3699631\charrsid13773120 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 
ing him. Well I went in bugger I said, let him stand on his legs. Fight on your feet, I said, not - not knock the poor bugger when he's over. Oh bugger, I had four or five catch hold of me, threw me back.
