man said, hey - you can pack up, you can pack up, see? But soon - soon as he found out that - your - your age, what your age was he'd send you home. Else they could be summonsed. For keeping you on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 There were strict regulations about the number of hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Oh yes. They wouldn't let ee work - they wouldn't let ee work if they knowed you wasn't up to age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 When you were at school before you left school entirely how many hours a day would you do at the job in the mill then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 
Well you - you'd go work Mondays, see, Tuesday you go school, Wednesday you'd go - work. Thursday school. Friday work. Saturday - you'd be home. See? Well then - you'd go picking apple
s when apples is about. Worked one day, school next. Work. See. All like that. And of course when you were - when you worked Fridays - you wouldn't go to school Saturdays. See? Well then you'd have that day yourself, whether - if there's apple picking you
'd go apple picking, if - wasn't - you'd go - go out and sew what you could - pick up somewhere. Somebody would - run an errand for anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 How did you get the job in the mill in the first place? Who got the job for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Oh you go up and see the foreman. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Who told you about it though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 
Go up and see the foreman and ask him - ask him whether he wants a boy. And he say yes. And then you'd - he'd tell you when you can start. See? Then you'd - tell your schoolmaster. Then he'd - put it right for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2584255\charrsid13773120 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 e.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Did a lot of the boys work in the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 'H yes, boys - boys and maidens worked half time, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 What exactly did you have to do in this job?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 In the spinning? Tie on ends. And slipping - slip bobbins. See, the - the - of 
the - the wool - the - the things be made up - they'm up - up here. Well they come - come whizzing round like that. Then they wind them round a bobbin. See? Well when that bobbin's through you - take it off and start a new one. See? They keep filling up. 
And you keep throwing them in a - in a hamper. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Is this what you did when you left school and worked full time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 No. When I - when I was half time - I done that. And then when I - finished - when I got a bit tall - the foreman wanted - wanted 
a chap over packing job. See? Of course he - he took me on. And then I went from spinning shop on a packing job. As a - grow tall. You know. So I went down there. Used to fetch errands. Fetch - fetch the stuff for the men work, what they wanted. And then 
- cut the wrapper. They call 'em wrappers you know, the - when the bales have been packed up. Well then you See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 What hours did you have to do at this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Ay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 What kind of hours did you work for this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Oh six - you went in your job six o'clock 'til six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 That was Saturday as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Ay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Was that Saturday as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Yes. Six days a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 And you'd have Sunday off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 What were the yours like when you were doing it part time? When you were spinning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Oh - same, six o'clock - six o'clock 'til six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 So you'd do six 'til six one day and school the next?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 School the next. That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 What kind of money were you paid for the part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Eighteen pence. Eighteen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2584255\charrsid13773120  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 pence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 That's for the part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 That's right. When I went I was having half a crown. Full time that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Did you feel it was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Ay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Did you think it was a fair wage for that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Oh bugger, no. Yes, by - by l
aw, and half a crown a week. But married men - married men - didn't get more than sixteen shilling a week, and they was - called smart. Twelve thirteen. Man - man - a man, he worked for twelve bob a week. Perhaps thirteen. Some would take fourteen. See? A
 man that had sixteen bob, he's smart.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 What kind of man would that be, would it be a same man working in the mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Yes, same man work in the mill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Did you ever give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Ay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Oh every Friday night give her the half a crown.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Did you give her the entire lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Yes. Her'd give you - give you perhaps - penny or tuppence back. To spend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 What would you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Sweets. That's to start w
ith, then - when you got mixed up with other chaps and - going in with - when you're going to work - working for a farm you'd get a shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Did you ever spend money on cigarettes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Yes, I used to boy a packet of cigarettes, five - for a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 How did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Oh - all right. One - one chap He wouldn't work, the bugger he'd - sleep - be always - sleeping. Go up in the loft and had a sleep.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Wouldn't anyone know he was missing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Ay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Wouldn't anyone know he was missing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2584255\charrsid13773120 Oh Us should be put on}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 
 - us shall be put on piecework. So I said, you and your bloody sleeping, I said, if you go sleeping, I said, I'm going to tell the bloody boss. Then I said, I shall have to have a fresh f
ellow. But of course there was a man leaving there - under rigger, what they call a rigger - and he asked for that job. See? So of course - I had a - a chap, he's still living, he'd tell you the same, Billy Roberts - I had ee from spinning shop over, and 
t
he - us is all going to be put on piecework. Boss - boss said to me he said - Billy - Billy Roberts is coming over here, he said, said he's - he's too big for our spinning job. He said, you can have ee. He said. He says, now - give you a fortnight to have
 
- I said, all right, I said. Of course when the boy come - I told him what he had to do. I showed him - everything, put the book. Then I says - you come - go down there and you'll find the pieces down there, put 'em on the trolley and then bring 'em up, I
 said and take - take all the - measurements, put 'em down singly, in fifty yards see, fifty yards, some was fifty-five, well fifty - fifty}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2584255\charrsid13773120  and a half, and some was fifty }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 one see. He had to put that down on this bit of paper. Then - the boss, he'd - cover t
hat off on his book see. When he - had 'em in. So - I showed him everything he had to do. And he got on so well with me - I thought myself well bugger I - I think - us shall earn more money piecework. So I said - here, I said, I'm going in to tell the bos
s
 - that - you'd good enough - you've learned it. Good enough for me. Us shall go on piecework next week. And - instead of I said you earning - fourteen bob I said - I said you'll be earning a pound. Oh that was - grand job see. And of course - he - he wor
k
ed like a bloody trouper you know. And of course - us had other jobs to do besides packing and that you know. There's - putting in the sheets, what they call sheets. That's shrinking, see? Us used to do that. But - but that's so much - so much a piece of 
t
hat. Us used to have so much a piece for - hanging up pieces. See? When you was steaming, what they call steaming you was day work. You put in the hours you - day work. Then you'd reckon up - reckoning it up. and that finished Wednesdays. Used to hand you
r time in Thursday mornings. And Friday nights you'd get paid.
\par 
