\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 
No, no. No. I wasn't working the gas board then. See when I worked in the Abby. I was - going there every day. See, no - nowhere else. 'Course - winter mornings - sometimes, some mornings I've been there - six o'clock. Get the horse r
eady, specially if they're - wanting stones - brought up. Well then - then when the is shifting summertime - been there five o'clock in the morning. Well I've been there nearly all night, day and night, in Abb}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2584255\charrsid13773120 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 y.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 So when did you start work in the Abbey then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Well I - that's I - thinking - I went out to Brent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2584255\charrsid13773120 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 s - and I come home - come home, and started work for a - man. And I worked for ee - three days. Well then I - worked for - worked for the gas company. Then I worked - oh I should say just - 
couple of year. Couple of year after I come - come home from Brent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2584255\charrsid13773120 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 
s. Then I worked for - a man called Mr Boyer, carpenter, he was a carpenter you know. I've done a job for ee on an old church. And of course then - he - in the Abbey you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2584255\charrsid13773120 p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 lent
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2584255\charrsid13773120 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 
 of work for him. Well he said - I - I'll send a chap her to ee, he said, just suit you. And he come over and he said, Freddy, he said, I want for you, he said, to - go in Abbey and ask for And tell the - he that chap that Mr Boyer send ee. So I went in
 and see him. Well he said, well you come on tomorrow morning, he said, cracking stones? I said, yes, I said. So I - I went home. And I went and see the man. I asked him whether he had a - stone hammer he could let me have. Well, he said, Fred, he said, I
 
can't let you have a stone hammer, not a proper one 'cos I haven't got none here. He said, I got the heads to 'em, he said, I've got three or four heads here. So he says, you'll have to go and get a stick. He said. Well I - he told me what sort of stick, 
g
et ash stick. He said, you get ash stick, he said, for they - they he said. I said, right. So I went up in a field - and cut four or five sticks, and then I went home and fixed - fixed couple in. And I went and see the chap, they made - made me a couple o
f
 little - wedges. About half inch long. And - now as soon as they get slack - soon as they get slack used to drive one of they in. Then you see up - tighten it up. Yes. So he - he made - well he worked in the mill. Called Ed Beare, he made 'em for me. And
 - I went in here, started - cracking stones, that was first job -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 So you only worked for the gas board for about two or three years and you worked for the Buckfast Abbey for the rest of the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 You were driving the horses most of the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 That's right. Fetching up the stones and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 You did that right through to the end of the second world war did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 What did you do after you lost your sight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 Ay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4329482 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 What happened when you lost your sight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 
Oh I - I come home, and - I was over in Newton - Newton Hospital for six months. Bugger they could keep me there - keep me there 'til now I think. And - well anyway I - they was - shifting home about - and I said, well can I go home Oh they said
, yes, Mr Oxenham. Right. So over come the chap and - took me home. He come over and - he said - when us go near in Ashburton he said - could ee do with a pint of cider? He says, well us'll stop down here, he said. He said, it's very good cider in there t
h
ey say. We stopped in Exeter Inn, and went up here, had a couple of pints and come home. And - I started making - what you call it - mats you know. Started making they. Rugs as they call 'em. Started making they. Oh I sold any - sold any amount of they, m
ade amount of 'em. Well then I started going over Newton to classes, making - chairs, stools, and - baskets. And - oh - when you start a job}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11156972\charrsid13773120  over there? Mrs Wakum, Mrs Waku}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 m from Exeter, her make you finish it. No matter how - how long it took, see. Well wh
en - I done - chairs you know and stuffed 'em. Well - doctor - Ironsides - her had a - four, five chairs. Her - send a boy down, for all that I could do. Well - I said - oh yes, I said
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 So he said, yes, he said. So I said - you bring 'em down, bring d
own one - I said, and I'll - feel 'em, then I said, I'll tell you, I said, whether I can - perform it. So he brought 'em down and - I gave him - I said - yes, I said, I think I can do this. He said, all right. So - he said, what about the stuff? Oh, I sai
d
, I'll get Miss Wakum I said to get that. I said, her get - get it cheaper either than what - you can or Mrs - the doctor can. I said, her get - get it - cheaper. So - got the - her brought me a lot, so - I said, how much - how much is that - how much is 
t
his Mrs Wakum? Oh, she said, not very much, her said, Mr Oxenham, her said, her said - I've got to see the doctor. So when her told the doctor and - how much it was see - then I started. And - I done the first one, and of course I - I stuffed them you kno
w
 so that - they wouldn't sink down. Oh - I done ee, I told the boy, here you are, I said, I've finished your - that chair. I said, come - come down after it then when you like. So - all right, he said, I'll come. So - he come down and - true enough the do
c
tor examine it. Mrs Morgan examine it. Oh it's splendid, splendid job. See? So of course - they send another one down. So I done ee. Well when I'm doing the fourth one, Mrs Wakum come, see. So her said - Mr Oxenham, she said, you're stuffing 'em too tight
.
 I said to her I said, well, I said, I've done - they've been pleased with it. Oh well, her said, you know well that's hard - bit hard. I said, it will get soft won't it? Her said, I don't think so. Well, I said - anyway - I - I didn't stuff ee so hard. W
ell - do you know - he sink - he sinked down. See?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13517188 WO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8796356\charrsid13773120 
But the others didn't. But they was comfortable to sit on like I said. So - the boy he - boy told Mrs see. He said, that - chair he said, the fourth one, he said, he don't - ain't so nice as others. 
Her said, that was through Mrs Wakum. Her said Mrs Wakum said he was stuffing 'em too tight. So - I said - well off you go, I said, you bring him down, I said, and I'll do it again. So - he brought him down and - I done him. Ripped off so much, see, and t
hen I stuffed again. And I done it all again. I had some stuff over. And then I - I done the fifth one. And - I charged 'em - what I - what I - price I ought to, and they give me - give me extra, give me more money than what I charged 'em.
